data.description: Tucked on a quiet street within the coveted Serenity Ridge neighborhood, this 3 bed, 2 bath Richmond Alcott ranch, boasts nearly 4,000 sq ft. The main floor offers one-level living and consists of a family room w/cozy fireplace for chilly Colorado nights, a kitchen w/island seating + direct access to the large patio and backyard—perfect for entertaining family + friends, a dining area, the primary bedroom w/ensuite bath and walk-in closet, 2 secondary beds, a hall bath, flex space (could be formal dining/office/4th bedroom) + laundry. The 1900 sq ft + unfinished basement offers a multitude of possibilities—create extra living space, a guest room, a bathroom, an exercise room, a home theatre, etc. The 2-car attached garage has plenty of room for all of your bikes, skis and camping/climbing gear. Enjoy a BBQ, stargaze, host an outdoor movie night or spend the evening around a fire pit roasting s’mores in your backyard. Tons of storage options. A++ location. Walk or pedal to Southlands-Bent Barley Brewing Co, Legends Coffee, The Alley, Wine Experience, Pho 90, Sweet Basil Cafe ++ so much more (restaurants, work out studios, bookstores, popular shopping). Trails and parks just out your back door. Top-rated Cherry Creek schools. Close proximity to Aurora Reservoir, Blackstone Country Club + Golf Course, and Saddle Rock Golf Course. Conveniently located near E-470. The last ranch home to sell in Serenity ridge (MLS #4205729), had a finished basement and sold in August for $810,000 in just 2 days. Patsburg is priced to sell @ $599,900. Seller's have an assumable loan on the home. The interest rate is 4.875 and the balance due is roughly $422,000.
